    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU2 VAD hemolysis prediction has been reviewed. Despite multiple credibility factor gaps relative to MRL 5 requirements, the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on primary inputs and the pressure-rise validation against FDA benchmark data provide sufficient confidence for the intended regulatory submission context. The assessment team accepts the evidence package with documented gaps, noting that six factors remain not-assessed and that aleatory uncertainty characterization for the flow-field validation result relies on qualitative expert judgment rather than structured probabilistic analysis.",
